5:
Did you lose your last brain cell, or
are you just stupid?
15:
Taiga and the rest already
explained that those clothes are
meant to reign you in, right?
17:
Using your power recklessly is
dangerous. How many times does
this make? Don't lie—I know you're
using it all the time.
21:
Little late for the scolding. I already
used it, all right? Only thing to do
now is wait.
23:
Besides, I'll get back to normal faster
if I cut loose and let everything air
out.
32:
I get it, okay? But I don't think you
got the right to criticize me.
35:
I know if you were in my position,
you'd have done the same thing.
You've got a history of being
reckless.
40:
When it happens, we'll make sure to
scold Alk as well. Also, going by that
logic, you don't have the right to
criticize Alk either.
42:
If your positions were reversed, you
wouldn't so easily forgive Alk.
50:
Neither of you should push
yourselves like that.
55:
All right, all right. I was gonna take it
easy anyway, even without your
hounding. Could use a few days off
to relax.
68:
I need a weapon—one I can use
without moving my arms and legs
separately.
71:
Hm. Okay, I understand why YOU
came to see me...
74:
But why are the rest of you in my
room?
84:
Don't worry about us. We're just here
to watch.
88:
So... What kind of weapon do you
have in mind?
95: In my dream, I used a barrel.
102:
I swear, you are impossible to
understand half the time...
110:
What's there not to understand?
Dreams sometimes tell us things we
don't yet know about ourselves.
115:
Yeah, I sometimes get hit with
inspiration when I'm sleeping too.
Bryce, do you get enough sleep?
120:
Listen here... Unlike you natural
geniuses, I have to put in the work to
make progress.
123:
...I suppose we'll just have to lay the
groundwork first.
129:
Have a seat. I'm not really a good
conversationalist, but... Tell me more
about that dream.
134:
I can help you there. I'd rather be
listening to this than my students'
career choices and all that.
139:
As for me, I'll lend a hand with the
actual designing process.
149:
Heh, being helped by two
unparalleled geniuses... It's almost
as if I'm the one dreaming instead.
164:
...That went quite well. As you can
see, it's a barrel-shaped, nonlethal
elemental grenade that
incapacitates with a flash of bright
light.
174:
We can adjust the output if you
want. Which, by the way, also
means we can change the color
and shape of the explosion.
181:
Yes. With this, I can fight too. Thank
you.
184: What's this? Having fun without me?
187: Hanabi... Sorry, did I wake you up?
190:
Nooope. It's not even bedtime. No
need to apologize.
194:
More importantly, I want to test
something out.
218:
Told you it would. Stella, go for
another.
232:
Now that's a genuine smile on
Stella's face.
235:
We ended up with something totally
different than we planned.
239:
...As long as the output is adjusted, it
can have other uses.
242:
Although this method might be just
what she was looking for.
246:
Hanabi, we should try other shapes
too!
